==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mojarra
<hw>Mo*jar"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety> <def>Any
of certain basslike marine fishes (mostly of tropical seas, and having a
deep, compressed body, protracile mouth, and large silvery scales)
constituting the family <fam>Gerridae</fam>, as <spn>Gerres
plumieri</spn>, found from Florida to Brazil and used as food. Also, any
of numerous other fishes of similar appearance but belonging to other
families.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mokadour</ent>⟦br⟧
